  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EAbout 80 percent of adults\u0026rsquo; experience low back pain at some point in their lifetimes. It is the most common cause of job-related disability and a leading contributor to missed workdays. Most low back pain is acute or short term and lasts a few days to a few weeks.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EIn 2010, Low Back Pain jumped to third place, with only Ischemic Heart Disease and COPD ranking higher in a study that ranked the most burdensome conditions in the U.S. in terms of poor health from disease.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EPBM is rarely a stand-alone in the management of lower back pain. \u0026nbsp;A multifaceted approach is often yields the best outcomes.\u0026nbsp; Combining active and passive care with physical medicine and PBM are proving to be successful treatment strategies.\u0026nbsp; Join Dr. Chris Carraway for the August webinar as he discusses ways to Manage Back Pain with Super Pulsed Laser.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E"
}]]></Value>
